The House Armed Services Committeelast night proposed cutting President Reagan's funding requestfor the Strategic Defence Initiative program by 1.7 billiondlrs to 3.5 billion.    The committee also cut by more than half the amount thepresident requested for a rail system for strategic missiles.It approved 250 mln dlrs for the project during itsconsideration of the 1988 defence authorisation bill.    The committee's proposals must be adopted by the full Houseand Senate before becoming law. The administration's totalrequest for 1988 defence spending was 312 billion dlrs. REUTER&#3;